"Test — $area y $slope nativos
'<hr/>
f(x) = x^2 + 2*x + 3
'<h4>$area directo</h4>
'∫₀¹ x² dx ='$area{x^2 @ x = 0 : 1}
'∫₀² f(x) dx ='$area{f(x) @ x = 0 : 2}
'<h4>$slope directo</h4>
'f'(2) ='$slope{f(x) @ x = 2}
'<h4>$area en variable simple</h4>
A = $area{x^2 @ x = 0 : 1}
'A ='A
'<h4>$area dentro de matriz literal (sin función)</h4>
V = [$area{x^2 @ x = 0 : 1}; $area{x @ x = 0 : 2}]
'V ='V
'<h4>$slope dentro de función</h4>
dV(x) = $slope{f(x) @ x = x}
'dV(2) ='dV(2)
'<h4>$slope con renombrado de variable</h4>
dV2(x) = $slope{f(t) @ t = x}
'dV2(2) ='dV2(2)
